article.headline: Auburn 79, Miles 58
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Rasheem Barrett had 19 points, five rebounds and four assists to lead Auburn to a 79-58 victory over Miles College on Tuesday night. The Tigers (4-0) closed the first half with a 17-5 run and led 43-33 at the break. Auburn used a half-court trap to pressure Division III Miles (3-1) and built the lead to 58-38 in the second half. Andrew Jones led all scorers with 24 points for Miles. He hit 7 of 18 shots from the floor, including five 3-pointers. Three Miles players fouled out. Frank Tolbert added 18 points for Auburn, with 16 coming in the first half, and Korvotney Barber had 13 points and 14 rebounds. The game was part of second-round action in the South Padre (Texas) Invitational.
